benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from bundle

covered: Valid Deletion scenarios (TC01, TC05) including empty removal
Invalid input formats (TC06, TC09, TC22, TC19)
Query parameter handling (TC02, TC03, TC11, TC09, TC19, TC21)
Single and multiple customField removals (TC02, TC03)
Structure and data integrity checks via subsequent GETs (TC01, TC03, TC05, TC25)
gaps: Authorization specifics beyond 401/Unauthorized (e.g., 403 Forbidden) not explicitly tested
Caching behavior testing (ETag, Cache-Control) is not covered
Rate limiting / throttling scenarios are not tested
Pagination handling is not applicable to DELETE in this context or not tested for large datasets
Soft-delete semantics are not applicable here and not covered (if relevant to domain)
recommendations: Add a test explicitly validating 403 Forbidden for insufficient permissions
Introduce tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) on DELETE responses
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure stability under bursts
If applicable, add pagination-related tests only if the API supports paginated deletion or list-of-ids, else confirm no pagination is expected
Consider adding a dedicated test for idempotency and proper handling of repeated DELETE calls on the same resource
